the first

37:52.036 --> 37:57.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
black woman elected to Congress
in 1968, who
moved on to become the first
black woman to

37:58.042 --> 38:03.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
run as a major-party candidate
for president
in 1972.

38:03.515 --> 38:09.954 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It was a short-lived, but
memorable bid, with
the slogan "Unbought and
Unbossed." She said

38:10.054 --> 38:11.890 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
her campaign was for the
have-nots.

38:11.990 --> 38:16.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHIRLEY CHISHOLM, Presidential
Candidate:
I am not the candidate of black
America, although

38:16.528 --> 38:19.030 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
