as menopausal, addled, not
really up to the

41:38.363 --> 41:40.131 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
responsibility.

41:40.231 --> 41:45.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And then, just a
few years
later, Shirley Chisholm, who ran
for president

41:45.370 --> 41:52.243 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in the early 1970s, first
African-American
woman elected to Congress. So,
she jumped

41:52.343 --> 41:54.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that hurdle, but the presidency
was something
else altogether.

41:54.679 --> 41:56.481 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ELLEN FITZPATRICK: Right.

41:56.581 --> 42:00.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was on the national stage
from the moment
of her election, and she was a
vociferous

42:00.618 --> 42:06.391 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
critic of the Nixon
administration. She got
a lot of press. She was
well-known. But she

42:06.491 --> 42:13.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
too was really ridiculed when
she announced
her bid for the presidency in
1972, but she

42:13.598 --> 42:15.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
