way to the
convention.

42:15.566 --> 42:20.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you draw
from all of
this, Ellen Fitzpatrick, in
terms of lessons

42:20.338 --> 42:25.176 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for Hillary Clinton this year or
any other
woman who wants to be president?

42:25.276 --> 42:29.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELLEN FITZPATRICK: Well, I think
the most
striking thing that we're seeing
in contemporary

42:29.881 --> 42:36.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
politics is that now, in Hillary
Clinton,
there is a woman candidate who
has overcome

42:36.154 --> 42:42.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the biggest obstacles in the way
of the women
that preceded her, but there is
no failure

42:42.894 --> 42:48.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like success in this case,
because she has
been able to raise a lot of
money.

42:48.733 --> 42:56.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That sunk every previous
candidate. She has
strong support from her party.
Very few women

42:56.808 --> 43:04.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have been able to get that. A
high national
profile. And she is widely seen,
because of

43:04.449 --> 43:08.019 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
