capable in foreign
affairs.

43:08.119 --> 43:12.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, she's overcome these
prejudices, but she's
now seen as establishment.

43:12.256 --> 43:17.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Some would say,
looking at
the polls, that the main
obstacles she faces

43:17.495 --> 43:22.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
don't have to do with gender.
They have to
do whether it's the controversy
over the e-mails

43:22.633 --> 43:23.768 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or people say they don't trust
her.

43:23.868 --> 43:24.702 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ELLEN FITZPATRICK: Right.

43:24.802 --> 43:26.671 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do you read
that?

43:26.771 --> 43:29.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELLEN FITZPATRICK: The way I
read it is that
a lot of Americans will say
today that they're

43:29.640 --> 43:34.345 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
happy to vote for a woman
president, and they're
even enthusiastic about that.

43:34.445 --> 43:41.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's a huge reversal from the
early 20th
century. But they often will
say, I just don't

43:41.486 --> 43:49.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like that woman. And I think
that the way
that I read it is that it's hard
to imagine

43:49.193 --> 43:55.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
anyone overcoming all these
obstacles and
also having this likability,
universal likability

43:55.500 --> 43:58.102 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
factor that some seem to be
looking for.

43:58.202 --> 44:02.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What about the
fact, Ellen
Fitzpatrick, that, in the United
States, we

44:03.007 --> 44:10.515 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
elected an African-American
president before
we may elect a woman president?

44:10.615 --> 44:16.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELLEN FITZPATRICK: Well, that
was an important
moment in overcoming a long,
obviously, and

44:16.821 --> 44:23.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
torturous racial history in the
United States
of tremendous inequality in
political life.

44:23.494 --> 44:29.634 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the changes that occurred in
the Democratic
